name: Eric Dolphin Restaurant
address: Jl. Seririt- Singaraja, Tukadmungga, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1:
The seafood platter was probably the best seafood we had in Bali. The menu highlights were the grilled Mahi mahi, fish curry and yellow rice.

The staff was friendly and created a really good atmosphere.

The owner and their children kept our kids entertained throughout the dinner so we could enjoy our wonderful food!
review 2: What a treat! The fish menu is to die for and the staff is just lovely. Thank you for a great moment!
review 3: Staff was friendly and attentive.This restaurant is a good choice for seafood lovers looking for quality ingredients.
review 4: Best seafood we had in Bali‚Ä¶ and we ate a lot! Came here after booking a dolphin tour with them (once in a lifetime experience) going to come back a few times before we leave!
review 5: Nice people, good atmosphere but honestly I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this place. We ordered  grilled fish for two, and it didn‚Äôt worth the price. Fish was frozen and not tasty at all. The rest of the food was fried and portions really poor for 2 ppl. The only thing the we liked was the tuna skewers. Even fruit was not that good. We choose the place cause of the positive reviews, but honestly I don‚Äôt understand why. Maybe we‚Äôve just got unlucky. If you are looking for fresh fish is not the right place.

address: Tukadmungga, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1: It's a nice place to hang out, good service too, too bad the quality of their food isn't as nice as the place, they're cheap though. review 2:

The price is decent. Will definitely be back again.
review 3: Ugh this place was SO good. You know a place is legit when they don‚Äôt have English menus but the waitress was very helpful. We got the fried fish and chicken and omg‚Ä¶it was incredible. review 5: Good & fresh seafood, good vibes, decent price. Plenty of outdoor space and parking. They can cater for groups.

review 1: Although this place is located in the remote area, this place provides extraordinary food and beverage. They have a full spec of coffee menu and it tastes great. The food is also delicious and it comes from great ingredients. When in the night, this caf√® will give you a realxing vibes with soft music background.

review 3:
Very delicious, cheap and friendly service! I would highly recommend this place!

review 4: Wonderful and cozy place for coffee, rice dishes and other Main courses. Tucked away behind the rice fields it is a small oasis with coconut trees, Cocoa as well as coffee plants. Staff is really nice and the food is delicious and craftfully assembled at very fair prices. Worth taking the extra steps!
review 5:
We had lunch at this delightful spot in the afternoon. They have a diverse menu including dishes like nasi goreng, pizza, and even waffles. The family engaged us in pleasant conversation and were all incredibly friendly.

We returned in the evening and enjoyed another delicious meal. All in all, this place comes highly recommended!
